comment: * A parcelable class encapsulating account data for contacts that originate from a SIM card.

variables.name: ADN_EF_TYPE
variables.comment: EF type identifier for the ADN partition.

variables.name: FDN_EF_TYPE
variables.comment: EF type identifier for the FDN partition.

variables.name: SDN_EF_TYPE
variables.comment: EF type identifier for the SDN partition.

variables.name: mAccountName
variables.comment: * The account_name of this SIM account. See {@link RawContacts#ACCOUNT_NAME}.

variables.name: mAccountType
variables.comment: * The account_type of this SIM account. See {@link RawContacts#ACCOUNT_TYPE}.

variables.name: mSimSlotIndex
variables.comment:
* The slot index of the SIM card this account maps to. See {@link
         * android.telephony.SubscriptionInfo#getSimSlotIndex()}.

variables.name: mEfType
variables.comment:
* The EF type of the contacts stored in this account. One of
         * {@link #ADN_EF_TYPE}, {@link #SDN_EF_TYPE} or {@link #FDN_EF_TYPE}.
         *
         * EF type is the Elementary File type of the partition these contacts come from within the
         * SIM card.
         *
         * ADN is the "abbreviated dialing numbers" or the user managed SIM contacts.
         *
         * SDN is the "service dialing numbers" which are usually preloaded onto the SIM by the
         * carrier.
         *
         * FDN is the "fixed dialing numbers" which are contacts which can only be dialed from that
         * SIM, used in cases such as parental control.
